gameplay.gameboard

Class PiecePlacer

  • java.lang.Object
    • gameplay.gameboard.PiecePlacer

  • public class PiecePlacer
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is used as a placeholder for information stored in database about the opponents units and is used in Database import methods to set up all pieces on the board (Grid)
    See Also:
    Database, Unit, UnitType, Grid

        public PiecePlacer(int pieceId,
                   int matchId,
                   int playerId,
                   int positionX,
                   int positionY,
                   int unit_type_id)
        Sets the pieceId, matchId, playerId, position X, position Y, and unit_type_id for each piece.
        Parameters:
        pieceId - Sets the pieceId for the Piece.
        matchId - Sets the matchId for the piece.
        playerId - Sets the playerId for the piece.
        positionX - Sets the piece's x-position in accordance with Grid position.
        positionY - Sets the piece's y-position in accordance with Grid position.
        unit_type_id - Sets the unit type id for the piece.
        See Also:
        Unit, UnitType, Grid
